President Biden is awarding the National Medal of Science and the National Medal of Technology and Innovation to individuals who have made significant contributions in science, technology, and innovation. The National Medal of Science is the highest scientific honor in the United States, recognizing outstanding achievements in various fields. The National Medal of Technology and Innovation, on the other hand, celebrates technological advancements that have improved the economy and quality of life. These awards exemplify the spirit of American possibility and highlight the impact of science and technology in solving complex problems and delivering innovative solutions. The recipients have made breakthroughs in medicine, combating the opioid epidemic, enhancing food security, promoting accessibility, protecting democracy, and more. Their work not only advances American leadership in these areas but also inspires future generations.